Package: station8
Title: Push knitted RMarkdown reports to a Station 8 hub
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Station 8", "Contributors", email = "station8@users.noreply.github.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Registers a hook that, after every HTML knit, prompts the user
    to push the rendered HTML to a Station 8 research hub. macOS shows a
    native dialog; Windows uses PowerShell; Linux uses zenity or console.
    Identity is a sha256 of the .Rmd absolute path so re-knits update the
    same report.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    knitr,
    httr2,
    digest,
    jsonlite,
    curl,
    tools
SystemRequirements: macOS osascript, or Windows PowerShell, or Linux zenity (optional)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
